cs.DC, cs.CC, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper deals with real-time collaboration among geographically distributed users, which falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): Although the paper does not explicitly deal with computational complexity, the use of Operational Transformation (OT) for consistency maintenance in collaborative editing can be seen as a technique to reduce the complexity of handling concurrent updates. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses how web applications can be designed to use the presented approach, which falls under the scope of software engineering. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents a new approach for simultaneous editing of shared JSON objects, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms for consistency maintenance. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The presented approach can be implemented in almost any modern web framework, which involves the use of programming languages for web development.
